            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41354",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aphillipo",
                        "name": "aphillipo",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Phillipo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, this is extremely strange behaviour; I have been trying to figure out why it is doing this, so thanks for the bug report to know that I'm not going mad.  I have no idea how to build a normalselect box in Zend forms, will post here when I figure it out.  Seems like creating a normal, simple select box should be simpler, but then that could be said about so much of zend.\r\n\r\nPlease fix.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aphillipo",
                        "name": "aphillipo",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Phillipo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-06T02:54:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-06T02:54:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42214",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=4sak3n0ne",
                        "name": "4sak3n0ne",
                        "displayName": "Justin Jahn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A [ZFForums|http:\/\/www.zfforums.com\/zend-framework-general-discussions-1\/general-q-zend-framework-2\/form-select-defaults-multi-when-name-ends-4900.html#post16675] article describes a temporary fix for this issue.\r\n\r\n{code:title=ZFForums|borderStyle=solid}\r\n<?php\r\n    $element = new Zend_Form_Element_Select('selectbox', array('multiple' => false ));\r\n    $element->setIsArray(true);\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=4sak3n0ne",
                        "name": "4sak3n0ne",
                        "displayName": "Justin Jahn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-09-08T13:40:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-09-08T13:40:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/52976",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cmiwebstudio",
                        "name": "cmiwebstudio",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Steinmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree this it a temporary fix, however, there are circumstances where this wouldn't be an option (creating a new instance).  One should be able to getElement and add this setIsArray attribute and NOT automatically turn your select into a multi select.  This is oversight at best.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cmiwebstudio",
                        "name": "cmiwebstudio",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Steinmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-12-26T23:58:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-12-26T23:58:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/52977",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cmiwebstudio",
                        "name": "cmiwebstudio",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Steinmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I should also mention this issue stil exists in Zf 1.12.1 many years after this issue was reported.",
